Breeding.description: Cassin's Auklets are slightly smaller than Parakeet Auklets, with a bill that's less thick and is dark gray, instead of orange. Cassin's are uniformly gray (including underparts) and they lack the Parakeet's long streak behind the eye.

Breeding adult.description: Rhinoceros Auklets are larger than Parakeet Auklets, with a longer and less thick bill. They have 2 face streaks and gray underparts, unlike Parakeet's single streak and white underparts.

Breeding.description: Breeding Tufted Puffins have a white face and extravagant gold-yellow head plumes that sweep behind the head, unlike Parakeet Auklet's dark face and thin white face streak.

Nonbreeding.description: Nonbreeding Tufted Puffins are larger than Parakeet Auklets, and are uniformly gray-brown without Parakeet's white chest and belly.
